# Git attributes for the subclaw repository.
#
# Helps GitHub Linguist correctly identify the project's primary language
# and ensures consistent line endings across platforms.

# Default behavior: detect text files and normalize line endings to LF on commit.
# But the original repo used CRLF, so we keep CRLF for source files.
* text=auto eol=crlf

# Python: always LF inside the file (Pythonic standard), but the .gitattributes
# is set to CRLF for the rest of the repo. The file is detected by extension.
*.py text eol=lf

# Shell scripts: must be LF for POSIX compatibility.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Markdown: render in GitHub with whatever the file has.
*.md text

# YAML: must be LF.
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf

# TOML: must be LF.
*.toml text eol=lf

# JSON: must be LF (some parsers are strict about line endings).
*.json text eol=lf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
*.html text eol=lf
*.txt text eol=lf
*.dockerignore text eol=lf
.gitignore text eol=lf

# Dockerfiles: must be LF.
Dockerfile text eol=lf

# Makefile: must be LF.
Makefile text eol=lf

# License: keep as-is (LF is fine, but CRLF also works).
LICENSE text eol=lf

# Binary files: do not touch.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.svg binary

# Git LFS: not currently used, but reserve for future binary assets.
# *.tar.gz filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Exclude vendored / generated files from diffs and language stats.
docs/awesome-list-submissions.md linguist-documentation
docs/seo-keywords.md linguist-documentation
docs/blog-post-devto.md linguist-documentation
docs/show-hn-post.md linguist-documentation
llms.txt linguist-documentation
llms-full.txt linguist-documentation
